# Admin dashboard — responsive UI

## Viewport tiers (`lib/dashboard-viewport.ts`)

| Tier | Width | Chrome |
|------|-------|--------|
| Mobile | < 768px | Hamburger nav, compact padding, card lists |
| Tablet | 768–1023px | Single-column sections, sidebar via overlay |
| Laptop+ | ≥ 1024px | Fixed sidebar (`lg`), multi-column grids |

## Utilities (`lib/dashboard-ui.ts`)

- `dbPageStack` — vertical section rhythm
- `dbPageHeaderRow` — title + actions header
- `dbHeaderActions` — 2-col button grid on mobile, inline on `sm+`
- `dbTableShell` — horizontal scroll fallback for tables
- `dbKpiGrid`, `dbSectionGrid` — responsive stat/section grids

## Split layouts (`components/dashboard/DashboardViewport.tsx`)

Use `DbMobileBlock` / `DbDesktopBlock` when mobile needs card stacks and desktop keeps tables:

```tsx
<DbMobileBlock>{/* card list */}</DbMobileBlock>
<DbDesktopBlock className={dbTableShell}>{/* table */}</DbDesktopBlock>
```

## Subtext (descriptions)

- **Sentence case** — capitalize only the first word (and proper nouns/acronyms).
- **End with a period.**
- Use `PageSubtitle` or `CardDescription` — do **not** rely on `toTitleCase` for descriptions.
- Titles/headings may still use `toTitleCase` via `PageTitle`, `CardTitle`, `SectionHeading`.

## Page headers

Prefer `DashboardPageHeader` with `dbHeaderActions` for action rows on dashboard and list pages.
